	<td width="501" align="RIGHT" valign="TOP">
		
	
	<table width="95%" border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0">
	
	<tr>
		<td><font face="Arial" size="3" color="#078D10"><b>Massive Software</b></font></td>
		<td></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td><font face="Arial" size="2"><p>In a bit of an Interview frenzy at the moment, I asked loads of people for interviews and got more responses than expected. So here it is, Massive Software the team working on <a href="http://www.quake3mods.net/fmj/">Full Metal Jacket</a> </p></font></td>
	</tr>
	
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#078D10">Question:</font> What is special about your mod. Why will people play it rather than something like Urban Terror or Snipers?

		</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#a0a108">Answer:</font> I think our mod will bring back the atmosphere of the movie,which is very impressive.Also there is something new in this mod : more outdoor levels than before.We want to create a realism vietnam theme with a great scenario around it.
And also we`ll have great map object like tanks,helicopters and other army vehicels.But maybe the people will play the other mods , I don`t know :-) But my favourite isn`t Urban Terror , it`s Survival 9 mm.</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td align="CENTER">
	 <font face="Arial" size="1"></font></td></tr>
	 
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#078D10">Question:</font> Why have you chosen to develop for Q3A rather than UT.      
		</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#a0a108">Answer:</font> To this topic I have to say a lot:
First the main reason is that the quake community is the biggest.<Br>
Other reasons are that I don`t really like ut and we think that it`s easier to make a mod for quake3.Also there are more features than in the UT engine:for example curved surfaces.Some of these features are really important for our mapdesign.<br>
I don`t want to say that UT`s engine is bad, but Q3A really kicks ass.
John Carmack is the greatest.</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td align="CENTER">
	 <font face="Arial" size="1"></font></td></tr>
	 
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#078D10">Question:</font> Have Massive Software dabbled developing in any other mods before?      
		</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#a0a108">Answer:</font> No we`re are new in the mod community but you can expect more mods after this one.</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td align="CENTER">
	 <font face="Arial" size="1"></font></td></tr>
	 
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#078D10">Question:</font> Will there be any game modes other than teamplay and DM?      
		</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#a0a108">Answer:</font> Yes a third mode: It`s called "Capture the rifles".There is no real new game play, it`s a ctf variant which plays during the vietnam war.You have to steal weapon boxes out of the camp of your enemy.But there`ll be several little gameplay changes</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td align="CENTER">
	 <font face="Arial" size="1"></font></td></tr>
	 
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#078D10">Question:</font> Is there a release date for FMJ yet?      
		</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#a0a108">Answer:</font> Good question, we`re trying to release first beta in late april.Maybe this one will only contain a few maps.But that`s not a promise.We`re working hard to get this mod out.
</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td align="CENTER">
	 <font face="Arial" size="1"></font></td></tr>
	 
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#078D10">Question:</font> Do you prefer AQ2 or CounterStrike?      
		</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#a0a108">Answer:</font> I like both very much.But I would say that CS is a bit more professionel.The models and levels are really impressive.So I play more CS than AQ2, but AQ2 was a revolution in the mod community, so I think the real innovation was AQ2</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td align="CENTER">
	 <font face="Arial" size="1"></font></td></tr>
	 
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#078D10">Question:</font> What style of realism do you plan to incorpoate into your mod, the furious action of AQ2 or the slower, more team based Counter Strike style?	</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#a0a108">Answer:</font> We are trying to include both in our mod. There will be a mode called "FREE FOR MARINES" which is more like AQ2 gameplay. It`s faster gameplay than the main mode "VIETNAM WAR". This mode is teamplay with tactical elements like in counterstrike.But we don`t copy counterstrike, we`ll make our own mod,which has its own features.
</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td align="CENTER">
	 <font face="Arial" size="1"></font></td></tr>
	 
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#078D10">Question:</font> We know you have chosen a Vietnamese theme. Can we expect proper Vietnam weapons?      
		</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#a0a108">Answer:</font> Yes.We decided to make the weapons different.If you`re choosing VIETCONG ,you will have an AK47 as default weapon, on the marines side you`ll have M16.
We want to implent the most weapons used during vietnam to make the mod realistic.</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td align="CENTER">
	 <font face="Arial" size="1"></font></td></tr>
	 
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#078D10">Question:</font> Why have you chosen to develop for Q3A rather than UT.      
		</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#a0a108">Answer:</font> <p>To this topic I have to say a lot:
First the main reason is that the quake community is the biggest.<Br>
Other reasons are that I don`t really like ut and we think that it`s easier to make a mod for quake3.Also there are more features than in the UT engine:for example curved surfaces.Some of these features are really important for our mapdesign.<br>
I don`t want to say that UT`s engine is bad, but Q3A really kicks ass.<Br>
John Carmack is the greatest.</p></font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td align="CENTER">
	 <font face="Arial" size="1"></font></td></tr>
	 
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#078D10">Question:</font> Will leg shots result in a limp?      
		</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#a0a108">Answer:</font> Maybe we`ll implent this in the second release.For the first one it`s not planned.
</font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td align="CENTER">
	 <font face="Arial" size="1"></font></td></tr>
	 
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><p>The Vietnam war is a great theme that I don`t think has been `mod`ified before. Could be a great game.<Br> For more info on
<a href="http://www.quake3mods.net/fmj/">Full Metal Jacket</a> visit the website at <a href="http://www.quake3mods.net/fmj/">http://www.quake3mods.net/fmj/</a> </p></font></td></tr>
	 <tr><td><font face="Arial" size="2"><p align="right"><a href="mailto:mdbigg@bigfoot.com">Trinity</font></a></p></td></tr>
	 
	</table>
	</td></tr></table>

